    • Constructor Detail

      • SnmpV3UsmUser

        @Since(value="7.0")
public SnmpV3UsmUser(String access,
                   String name,
                   String password,
                   String passphrase,
                   String secLevel)
        The SNMP v3 usmUser object is used with the API method SetSnmpInfo to configure SNMP on the cluster.
        Parameters:
        access - [required]
        rouser: read-only access.*
        name - [required] The name of the user. Must contain at least one character, but no more than 32 characters. Blank spaces are not allowed.
        password - [required] The password of the user. Must be between 8 and 255 characters long (inclusive). Blank spaces are not allowed. Required if "secLevel" is "auth" or "priv."
        passphrase - [required] The passphrase of the user. Must be between 8 and 255 characters long (inclusive). Blank spaces are not allowed. Required if "secLevel" is "priv."
        secLevel - [required]
        noauth: No password or passphrase is required.
        Since:
        7.0

    • Method Detail

      • getAccess

        public String getAccess()

        rouser: read-only access.*
        rwuser: for read-write access.
        rosys: for read-only access to a restricted set of system information *SolidFire recommends that all USM users be set to "rouser" access, because all SolidFire MIB objects are read-only.

      • getName

        public String getName()
        The name of the user. Must contain at least one character, but no more than 32 characters. Blank spaces are not allowed.

      • getPassword

        public String getPassword()
        The password of the user. Must be between 8 and 255 characters long (inclusive). Blank spaces are not allowed. Required if "secLevel" is "auth" or "priv."

      • getPassphrase

        public String getPassphrase()
        The passphrase of the user. Must be between 8 and 255 characters long (inclusive). Blank spaces are not allowed. Required if "secLevel" is "priv."

      • getSecLevel

        public String getSecLevel()

        noauth: No password or passphrase is required.
        auth: A password is required for user access.
        priv: A password and passphrase is required for user access.
